  "response": "Goldman Sachs' compensation structure typically includes a mix of base salary and discretionary bonuses, which can vary significantly by division and individual performance. While exact details can change yearly, here's a general overview:\n\n1. Investment Banking Division (IBD):\n- Base salary: $85,000-$120,000 for analysts\n- Total compensation: $150,000-$350,000 for junior bankers\n- Senior bankers can earn significantly more, potentially $500,000-$1M+\n\n2. Trading & Markets:\n- Base salary: $75,000-$150,000\n- Total compensation: $200,000-$500,000 for mid-level employees\n- Top performers can earn $1M+ \n\n3. Asset Management:\n- Base salary: $80,000-$150,000\n- Total compensation: $150,000-$400,000\n\n4. Technology Division:\n- Base salary: $100,000-$150,000\n- Total compensation: $150,000-$300,000\n\n5. Private Wealth Management:\n- Base salary varies\n- Often includes significant commission/performance-based compensation\n\nImportant notes:\n- Bonuses are discretionary and performance-based\n- Compensation can vary significantly by individual and market conditions\n- These are approximate ranges and can change annually",
